article.headline: Utah St. 68, CS Bakersfield 51
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Tai Wesley had 15 points and 10 rebounds to lead Utah State to a 68-51 victory against Cal State Bakersfield on Wednesday night. Tyler Newbold added 13 points for the Aggies (6-3), who committed just five turnovers, one in the first half. Stephon Carter scored 11 points and Trent Blakley 10 for the Roadrunners (1-7), who trailed 34-17 at halftime. A 27-2 run over a 12-minute period in the first half gave Utah State a commanding lead. The Aggies made 11 of 21 shots from the floor during the run.
